# Constant Function <B01>

The function <B01> is a constant function that always returns the value 1 regardless of the input. For any integer x that is passed to <B01>, the output will always be 1.

```
<B01>(0) = 1
<B01>(42) = 1
<B01>(-7) = 1
```

A key property of <B01> is that it has zero slope, meaning the derivative of this function is always 0. This makes <B01> useful in situations where you need a baseline function that remains unchanged regardless of input variations.
